  "assemblySteps": [
    "Four-Patch: Sew 1 Fabric B square to left side of 1 Fabric A square for top row. Sew 1 Fabric A square to left of 1 Fabric B square for bottom row. Join rows lengthwise. Make 12.",
    "Rail Fence: Sew 1 Fabric C strip to each side of 1 Fabric A strip. Make 12.",
    "Half-Square Triangle (HST): Layer 1 Fabric D square on 1 Fabric A square right sides together. Draw diagonal, sew 0.25 inch from each side, cut apart on line, press. Each pair yields 2 HST blocks. Make 16.",
    "Quarter-Square Triangle (QST) Version A: Sew 1 Fabric A triangle to 1 Fabric F triangle. Sew 1 Fabric E triangle to the AF unit along long sides. Trim to 6.5 inches. Make 4 Version A.",
    "Quarter-Square Triangle (QST) Version B: Repeat QST steps with reversed fabric placement per Diagram 2. Make 4 Version B.",
    "Hourglass: Cut Fabric A and Fabric G squares on both diagonals. Sew 1 Fabric A triangle to 1 Fabric G triangle to make AG unit. Join 2 AG units along long sides. Trim to 6.5 inches. Each square pair yields 2 blocks. Make 8.",
    "Birds in the Air: Make HST from Fabric A and Fabric I squares (stitch-and-flip method). Sew Fabric A triangles to HST unit to make Unit 2. Join Unit 2 with Fabric H large triangle along long sides. Trim to 6.5 inches. Make 16.",
    "Square in a Square: Place 1 Fabric J square on corner of Fabric A square, sew across diagonal, flip and press, trim. Repeat for all 4 corners. Make 4.",
    "Flying Geese: Stitch-and-flip Fabric A squares on each end of Fabric K strip to make Unit 1. Repeat with Fabric L strip to make Unit 2. Sew Unit 1 to top of Unit 2. Make 16.",
    "Pinwheel: Layer Fabric A and Fabric M squares, draw diagonal, sew 0.25 inch from each side, cut to yield 4 HST units. Arrange in pinwheel orientation and sew into 2 rows of 2. Join rows. Make 8.",
    "Arrange all 100 blocks in 10 rows of 10 blocks per the Quilt Layout diagram, paying attention to block orientations. Press seams to the right for odd rows and to the left for even rows.",
    "Sew the 10 pieced rows together lengthwise in numerical order to complete the quilt top.",
    "Layer quilt top with batting and backing. Quilt as desired.",
    "Sew binding strips together end to end with 45-degree seams. Fold lengthwise wrong sides together and press. Bind the quilt."
  ],
